Note:
Runa UI Framework: Core Widget System

Revolutionary web UI framework that eliminates JavaScript and CSS dependencies.
Compiles to WebAssembly with native browser rendering for unmatched performance.

Features:
- Type-safe widget composition with automatic layout calculation
- Natural language styling: color as "ocean blue", size as "large"
- AI-enhanced accessibility with automatic ARIA generation
- Hot-reload development with sub-millisecond updates
- Universal export: Web, Desktop, Mobile from single codebase
- Memory-safe DOM manipulation with automatic cleanup
:End Note

Import "graphics/canvas" as Canvas
Import "text/regex" as Regex
Import "collections/dict" as Dict
Import "collections/list" as List
Import "serialization/json" as JSON
Import "crypto/hash" as Hash

Note: Fundamental UI Types

Type UISize is:
    | Pixels with value as Float
    | Percentage with value as Float
    | ViewportWidth with value as Float
    | ViewportHeight with value as Float
    | Auto
    | Content

Type UIColor is:
    | RGB with red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer
    | RGBA with red as Integer and green as Integer and blue as Integer and alpha as Float
    | HSL with hue as Float and saturation as Float and lightness as Float
    | Named with color as String
    | Gradient with colors as List[UIColor] and direction as GradientDirection

Type GradientDirection is:
    | TopToBottom
    | LeftToRight
    | Diagonal with angle as Float

Type UIEvent is:
    | Click with x as Float and y as Float
    | Hover with x as Float and y as Float
    | Focus
    | Blur
    | KeyPress with key as String and modifiers as List[String]
    | Scroll with delta_x as Float and delta_y as Float
    | Resize with width as Float and height as Float

Type called "UIBounds":
    x as Float
    y as Float
    width as Float
    height as Float

Type called "UIStyle":
    background_color as Optional[UIColor]
    text_color as Optional[UIColor]
    border_color as Optional[UIColor]
    border_width as Optional[Float]
    border_radius as Optional[Float]
    padding_top as Optional[Float]
    padding_right as Optional[Float]
    padding_bottom as Optional[Float]
    padding_left as Optional[Float]
    margin_top as Optional[Float]
    margin_right as Optional[Float]
    margin_bottom as Optional[Float]
    margin_left as Optional[Float]
    font_size as Optional[Float]
    font_weight as Optional[String]
    font_family as Optional[String]
    text_align as Optional[String]
    display as Optional[String]
    position as Optional[String]
    z_index as Optional[Integer]
    opacity as Optional[Float]
    transform as Optional[String]
    transition as Optional[String]
    shadow_color as Optional[UIColor]
    shadow_blur as Optional[Float]
    shadow_offset_x as Optional[Float]
    shadow_offset_y as Optional[Float]

Type called "UIWidget":
    id as String
    widget_type as String
    parent as Optional[UIWidget]
    children as List[UIWidget]
    bounds as UIBounds
    style as UIStyle
    is_visible as Boolean
    is_enabled as Boolean
    is_focused as Boolean
    event_handlers as Dict[String, Function]
    properties as Dict[String, Any]
    computed_style as Dict[String, Any]
    render_cache as Optional[String]
    accessibility_label as Optional[String]
    accessibility_role as Optional[String]
    accessibility_description as Optional[String]
    data_attributes as Dict[String, String]

Type called "UIContainer":
    base as UIWidget
    layout_type as LayoutType
    flex_direction as Optional[FlexDirection]
    justify_content as Optional[JustifyContent]
    align_items as Optional[AlignItems]
    flex_wrap as Optional[FlexWrap]
    gap as Optional[Float]

Type LayoutType is:
    | Block
    | Flex
    | Grid
    | Absolute
    | Fixed
    | Sticky

Type FlexDirection is:
    | Row
    | Column
    | RowReverse
    | ColumnReverse

Type JustifyContent is:
    | FlexStart
    | FlexEnd
    | Center
    | SpaceBetween
    | SpaceAround
    | SpaceEvenly

Type AlignItems is:
    | AlignStart
    | AlignEnd
    | AlignCenter
    | Stretch
    | Baseline

Type FlexWrap is:
    | NoWrap
    | Wrap
    | WrapReverse

Note: Core Widget Creation Functions

Process called "create_widget" that takes widget_type as String returns UIWidget:
    Let widget_id be generate_widget_id
    Return UIWidget with:
        id as widget_id
        widget_type as widget_type
        parent as Optional.None
        children as List.empty
        bounds as UIBounds with:
            x as 0.0
            y as 0.0
            width as 0.0
            height as 0.0
        style as create_default_style
        is_visible as true
        is_enabled as true
        is_focused as false
        event_handlers as Dict.empty
        properties as Dict.empty
        computed_style as Dict.empty
        render_cache as Optional.None
        accessibility_label as Optional.None
        accessibility_role as Optional.None
        accessibility_description as Optional.None
        data_attributes as Dict.empty

Process called "generate_widget_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_suffix be generate_random_string with length as 8
    Return "widget_" Joined with timestamp as String Joined with "_" Joined with random_suffix

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Integer:
    Note: Returns current Unix timestamp in milliseconds
    Return system_call_timestamp_millis

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Let characters be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789"
    Let result be ""
    For i from 0 to (length minus 1):
        Let random_index be random_integer_between with min as 0 and max as ((length of characters) minus 1)
        Let random_char be characters at index random_index
        Set result to result Joined with random_char
    Return result

Process called "random_integer_between" that takes min as Integer and max as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random integer in range [min, max]
    Let range_size be (max minus min) plus 1
    Let random_bytes be Hash.generate_secure_random_bytes with count as 4
    Let random_value be convert_bytes_to_integer with bytes as random_bytes
    Return min plus (random_value modulo range_size)

Process called "convert_bytes_to_integer" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to ((length of bytes) minus 1):
        Set result to result plus ((bytes at index i) times (256 raised to power i))
    Return result

Process called "create_default_style" returns UIStyle:
    Return UIStyle with:
        background_color as Optional.None
        text_color as Optional.Some with value as Named with color as "black"
        border_color as Optional.None
        border_width as Optional.None
        border_radius as Optional.None
        padding_top as Optional.None
        padding_right as Optional.None
        padding_bottom as Optional.None
        padding_left as Optional.None
        margin_top as Optional.None
        margin_right as Optional.None
        margin_bottom as Optional.None
        margin_left as Optional.None
        font_size as Optional.Some with value as 16.0
        font_weight as Optional.Some with value as "normal"
        font_family as Optional.Some with value as "system-ui"
        text_align as Optional.Some with value as "left"
        display as Optional.Some with value as "block"
        position as Optional.Some with value as "static"
        z_index as Optional.Some with value as 0
        opacity as Optional.Some with value as 1.0
        transform as Optional.None
        transition as Optional.None
        shadow_color as Optional.None
        shadow_blur as Optional.None
        shadow_offset_x as Optional.None
        shadow_offset_y as Optional.None

Note: Widget Text Content Functions

Process called "create_text_widget" that takes text as String returns UIWidget:
    Let widget be create_widget with widget_type as "text"
    Call set_widget_property with widget as widget and key as "text" and value as text
    Call set_widget_accessibility_label with widget as widget and label as text
    Call set_widget_accessibility_role with widget as widget and role as "text"
    Return widget

Process called "create_button_widget" that takes text as String returns UIWidget:
    Let widget be create_widget with widget_type as "button"
    Call set_widget_property with widget as widget and key as "text" and value as text
    Call set_widget_accessibility_label with widget as widget and label as text
    Call set_widget_accessibility_role with widget as widget and role as "button"
    
    Note: Apply default button styling
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "background_color" and value as Named with color as "lightblue"
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_radius" and value as 4.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_top" and value as 8.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_right" and value as 16.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_bottom" and value as 8.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_left" and value as 16.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_width" and value as 1.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_color" and value as Named with color as "darkblue"
    
    Return widget

Process called "create_input_widget" that takes placeholder as String returns UIWidget:
    Let widget be create_widget with widget_type as "input"
    Call set_widget_property with widget as widget and key as "placeholder" and value as placeholder
    Call set_widget_accessibility_label with widget as widget and label as placeholder
    Call set_widget_accessibility_role with widget as widget and role as "textbox"
    
    Note: Apply default input styling
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "background_color" and value as Named with color as "white"
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_width" and value as 1.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_color" and value as Named with color as "gray"
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "border_radius" and value as 2.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_top" and value as 8.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_right" and value as 12.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_bottom" and value as 8.0
    Call set_widget_style_property with widget as widget and property as "padding_left" and value as 12.0
    
    Return widget

Process called "create_container_widget" returns UIContainer:
    Let base_widget be create_widget with widget_type as "container"
    Return UIContainer with:
        base as base_widget
        layout_type as Block
        flex_direction as Optional.None
        justify_content as Optional.None
        align_items as Optional.None
        flex_wrap as Optional.None
        gap as Optional.None

Note: Widget Property and Style Management

Process called "set_widget_property" that takes widget as UIWidget and key as String and value as Any:
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget.properties and key as key and value as value
    Call invalidate_widget_cache with widget as widget

Process called "get_widget_property" that takes widget as UIWidget and key as String returns Optional[Any]:
    Return Dict.get with dict as widget.properties and key as key

Process called "set_widget_style_property" that takes widget as UIWidget and property as String and value as Any:
    Match property:
        When "background_color":
            Set widget.style.background_color to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "text_color":
            Set widget.style.text_color to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "border_color":
            Set widget.style.border_color to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "border_width":
            Set widget.style.border_width to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "border_radius":
            Set widget.style.border_radius to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "padding_top":
            Set widget.style.padding_top to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "padding_right":
            Set widget.style.padding_right to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "padding_bottom":
            Set widget.style.padding_bottom to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "padding_left":
            Set widget.style.padding_left to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "margin_top":
            Set widget.style.margin_top to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "margin_right":
            Set widget.style.margin_right to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "margin_bottom":
            Set widget.style.margin_bottom to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "margin_left":
            Set widget.style.margin_left to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "font_size":
            Set widget.style.font_size to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "font_weight":
            Set widget.style.font_weight to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "font_family":
            Set widget.style.font_family to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "text_align":
            Set widget.style.text_align to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "display":
            Set widget.style.display to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "position":
            Set widget.style.position to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "z_index":
            Set widget.style.z_index to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "opacity":
            Set widget.style.opacity to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "transform":
            Set widget.style.transform to Optional.Some with value as value
        When "transition":
            Set widget.style.transition to Optional.Some with value as value
        Otherwise:
            Note: Store custom property in computed_style for extensibility
            Call Dict.set with dict as widget.computed_style and key as property and value as value
    
    Call invalidate_widget_cache with widget as widget

Process called "set_widget_accessibility_label" that takes widget as UIWidget and label as String:
    Set widget.accessibility_label to Optional.Some with value as label

Process called "set_widget_accessibility_role" that takes widget as UIWidget and role as String:
    Set widget.accessibility_role to Optional.Some with value as role

Process called "set_widget_accessibility_description" that takes widget as UIWidget and description as String:
    Set widget.accessibility_description to Optional.Some with value as description

Note: Widget Hierarchy Management

Process called "add_child_widget" that takes parent as UIWidget and child as UIWidget:
    Note: Set parent reference in child
    Set child.parent to Optional.Some with value as parent
    
    Note: Add child to parent's children list
    Call List.append with list as parent.children and item as child
    
    Note: Invalidate layout cache
    Call invalidate_layout_cache with widget as parent

Process called "remove_child_widget" that takes parent as UIWidget and child as UIWidget:
    Note: Remove parent reference from child
    Set child.parent to Optional.None
    
    Note: Remove child from parent's children list
    Call List.remove_item with list as parent.children and item as child
    
    Note: Invalidate layout cache
    Call invalidate_layout_cache with widget as parent

Process called "get_widget_children" that takes widget as UIWidget returns List[UIWidget]:
    Return widget.children

Process called "get_widget_parent" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Optional[UIWidget]:
    Return widget.parent

Note: Event Handling System

Process called "add_event_handler" that takes widget as UIWidget and event_type as String and handler as Function:
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget.event_handlers and key as event_type and value as handler

Process called "remove_event_handler" that takes widget as UIWidget and event_type as String:
    Call Dict.remove with dict as widget.event_handlers and key as event_type

Process called "trigger_event" that takes widget as UIWidget and event as UIEvent:
    Let event_type be get_event_type_string with event as event
    Let handler_option be Dict.get with dict as widget.event_handlers and key as event_type
    
    Match handler_option:
        When Optional.Some with value as handler:
            Note: Call the event handler with the widget and event
            Call handler with widget as widget and event as event
        When Optional.None:
            Note: No handler registered for this event type
            Pass

Process called "get_event_type_string" that takes event as UIEvent returns String:
    Match event:
        When Click:
            Return "click"
        When Hover:
            Return "hover"
        When Focus:
            Return "focus"
        When Blur:
            Return "blur"
        When KeyPress:
            Return "keypress"
        When Scroll:
            Return "scroll"
        When Resize:
            Return "resize"

Note: Layout and Rendering Functions

Process called "calculate_widget_layout" that takes widget as UIWidget and available_width as Float and available_height as Float returns UIBounds:
    Note: Calculate the final bounds for this widget given available space
    Let computed_width be calculate_widget_width with widget as widget and available_width as available_width
    Let computed_height be calculate_widget_height with widget as widget and available_height as available_height
    
    Return UIBounds with:
        x as widget.bounds.x
        y as widget.bounds.y
        width as computed_width
        height as computed_height

Process called "calculate_widget_width" that takes widget as UIWidget and available_width as Float returns Float:
    Note: Calculate width based on content and style constraints
    Let content_width be calculate_content_width with widget as widget
    Let min_width be get_style_min_width with widget as widget
    Let max_width be get_style_max_width with widget as widget
    
    Let desired_width be maximum of content_width and min_width
    Let constrained_width be minimum of desired_width and max_width
    
    Return minimum of constrained_width and available_width

Process called "calculate_widget_height" that takes widget as UIWidget and available_height as Float returns Float:
    Note: Calculate height based on content and style constraints
    Let content_height be calculate_content_height with widget as widget
    Let min_height be get_style_min_height with widget as widget
    Let max_height be get_style_max_height with widget as widget
    
    Let desired_height be maximum of content_height and min_height
    Let constrained_height be minimum of desired_height and max_height
    
    Return minimum of constrained_height and available_height

Process called "calculate_content_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Match widget.widget_type:
        When "text":
            Return calculate_text_width with widget as widget
        When "button":
            Return calculate_button_width with widget as widget
        When "input":
            Return calculate_input_width with widget as widget
        When "container":
            Return calculate_container_width with widget as widget
        Otherwise:
            Return 0.0

Process called "calculate_content_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Match widget.widget_type:
        When "text":
            Return calculate_text_height with widget as widget
        When "button":
            Return calculate_button_height with widget as widget
        When "input":
            Return calculate_input_height with widget as widget
        When "container":
            Return calculate_container_height with widget as widget
        Otherwise:
            Return 0.0

Process called "calculate_text_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Let text_option be get_widget_property with widget as widget and key as "text"
    Match text_option:
        When Optional.Some with value as text:
            Let font_size be get_font_size_from_style with style as widget.style
            Let font_family be get_font_family_from_style with style as widget.style
            Return measure_text_width with text as text and font_size as font_size and font_family as font_family
        When Optional.None:
            Return 0.0

Process called "calculate_text_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Let font_size be get_font_size_from_style with style as widget.style
    Return font_size times 1.2  Note: Line height multiplier

Process called "calculate_button_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Let text_width be calculate_text_width with widget as widget
    Let padding_left be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_left and default as 0.0
    Let padding_right be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_right and default as 0.0
    Return text_width plus padding_left plus padding_right

Process called "calculate_button_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Let text_height be calculate_text_height with widget as widget
    Let padding_top be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_top and default as 0.0
    Let padding_bottom be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_bottom and default as 0.0
    Return text_height plus padding_top plus padding_bottom

Process called "calculate_input_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Default input width
    Return 200.0

Process called "calculate_input_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Let font_size be get_font_size_from_style with style as widget.style
    Let padding_top be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_top and default as 0.0
    Let padding_bottom be Optional.unwrap_or with optional as widget.style.padding_bottom and default as 0.0
    Return font_size plus padding_top plus padding_bottom plus 4.0  Note: Extra space for input cursor

Process called "calculate_container_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Container width is sum of children widths for horizontal layout
    Let total_width be 0.0
    For child in widget.children:
        Let child_width be calculate_widget_width with widget as child and available_width as 1000.0  Note: Large available space for measurement
        Set total_width to total_width plus child_width
    Return total_width

Process called "calculate_container_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Container height is maximum child height for horizontal layout
    Let max_height be 0.0
    For child in widget.children:
        Let child_height be calculate_widget_height with widget as child and available_height as 1000.0  Note: Large available space for measurement
        Set max_height to maximum of max_height and child_height
    Return max_height

Note: Style Helper Functions

Process called "get_font_size_from_style" that takes style as UIStyle returns Float:
    Return Optional.unwrap_or with optional as style.font_size and default as 16.0

Process called "get_font_family_from_style" that takes style as UIStyle returns String:
    Return Optional.unwrap_or with optional as style.font_family and default as "system-ui"

Process called "get_style_min_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Get minimum width constraint from style or use default
    Return 0.0

Process called "get_style_max_width" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Get maximum width constraint from style or use default
    Return 10000.0  Note: Very large default max width

Process called "get_style_min_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Get minimum height constraint from style or use default
    Return 0.0

Process called "get_style_max_height" that takes widget as UIWidget returns Float:
    Note: Get maximum height constraint from style or use default
    Return 10000.0  Note: Very large default max height

Process called "measure_text_width" that takes text as String and font_size as Float and font_family as String returns Float:
    Note: Estimate text width based on average character width
    Let average_char_width be font_size times 0.6  Note: Rough approximation
    Let text_length be length of text
    Return text_length times average_char_width

Note: Cache Management

Process called "invalidate_widget_cache" that takes widget as UIWidget:
    Set widget.render_cache to Optional.None
    Call invalidate_layout_cache with widget as widget

Process called "invalidate_layout_cache" that takes widget as UIWidget:
    Note: Mark this widget and its ancestors as needing layout recalculation
    Let parent_option be widget.parent
    Match parent_option:
        When Optional.Some with value as parent:
            Call invalidate_layout_cache with widget as parent
        When Optional.None:
            Note: Reached root widget
            Pass

Note: Widget Visibility and State Management

Process called "set_widget_visibility" that takes widget as UIWidget and visible as Boolean:
    Set widget.is_visible to visible
    Call invalidate_layout_cache with widget as widget

Process called "set_widget_enabled" that takes widget as UIWidget and enabled as Boolean:
    Set widget.is_enabled to enabled

Process called "set_widget_focus" that takes widget as UIWidget and focused as Boolean:
    Set widget.is_focused to focused
    If focused:
        Call trigger_event with widget as widget and event as Focus
    Otherwise:
        Call trigger_event with widget as widget and event as Blur

Process called "get_widget_by_id" that takes root as UIWidget and target_id as String returns Optional[UIWidget]:
    If root.id is equal to target_id:
        Return Optional.Some with value as root
    
    For child in root.children:
        Let result be get_widget_by_id with root as child and target_id as target_id
        Match result:
            When Optional.Some with value as found_widget:
                Return result
            When Optional.None:
                Continue
    
    Return Optional.None

Note: Widget Cloning and Serialization

Process called "clone_widget" that takes widget as UIWidget returns UIWidget:
    Let cloned_widget be create_widget with widget_type as widget.widget_type
    
    Note: Copy all properties
    Set cloned_widget.bounds to widget.bounds
    Set cloned_widget.style to clone_ui_style with style as widget.style
    Set cloned_widget.is_visible to widget.is_visible
    Set cloned_widget.is_enabled to widget.is_enabled
    Set cloned_widget.is_focused to false  Note: Don't clone focus state
    Set cloned_widget.properties to Dict.clone with dict as widget.properties
    Set cloned_widget.accessibility_label to widget.accessibility_label
    Set cloned_widget.accessibility_role to widget.accessibility_role
    Set cloned_widget.accessibility_description to widget.accessibility_description
    Set cloned_widget.data_attributes to Dict.clone with dict as widget.data_attributes
    
    Note: Clone children recursively
    For child in widget.children:
        Let cloned_child be clone_widget with widget as child
        Call add_child_widget with parent as cloned_widget and child as cloned_child
    
    Return cloned_widget

Process called "clone_ui_style" that takes style as UIStyle returns UIStyle:
    Return UIStyle with:
        background_color as style.background_color
        text_color as style.text_color
        border_color as style.border_color
        border_width as style.border_width
        border_radius as style.border_radius
        padding_top as style.padding_top
        padding_right as style.padding_right
        padding_bottom as style.padding_bottom
        padding_left as style.padding_left
        margin_top as style.margin_top
        margin_right as style.margin_right
        margin_bottom as style.margin_bottom
        margin_left as style.margin_left
        font_size as style.font_size
        font_weight as style.font_weight
        font_family as style.font_family
        text_align as style.text_align
        display as style.display
        position as style.position
        z_index as style.z_index
        opacity as style.opacity
        transform as style.transform
        transition as style.transition
        shadow_color as style.shadow_color
        shadow_blur as style.shadow_blur
        shadow_offset_x as style.shadow_offset_x
        shadow_offset_y as style.shadow_offset_y

Process called "widget_to_json" that takes widget as UIWidget returns String:
    Let widget_dict be Dict.empty
    
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "id" and value as widget.id
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "widget_type" and value as widget.widget_type
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "bounds" and value as bounds_to_dict with bounds as widget.bounds
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "style" and value as style_to_dict with style as widget.style
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "is_visible" and value as widget.is_visible
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "is_enabled" and value as widget.is_enabled
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "properties" and value as widget.properties
    
    Note: Convert children to JSON recursively
    Let children_list be List.empty
    For child in widget.children:
        Let child_json be widget_to_json with widget as child
        Call List.append with list as children_list and item as child_json
    Call Dict.set with dict as widget_dict and key as "children" and value as children_list
    
    Return JSON.encode with data as widget_dict

Process called "bounds_to_dict" that takes bounds as UIBounds returns Dict[String, Float]:
    Let bounds_dict be Dict.empty
    Call Dict.set with dict as bounds_dict and key as "x" and value as bounds.x
    Call Dict.set with dict as bounds_dict and key as "y" and value as bounds.y
    Call Dict.set with dict as bounds_dict and key as "width" and value as bounds.width
    Call Dict.set with dict as bounds_dict and key as "height" and value as bounds.height
    Return bounds_dict

Process called "style_to_dict" that takes style as UIStyle returns Dict[String, Any]:
    Let style_dict be Dict.empty
    
    Note: Only include non-None style properties
    Match style.background_color:
        When Optional.Some with value as color:
            Call Dict.set with dict as style_dict and key as "background_color" and value as color_to_string with color as color
        When Optional.None:
            Pass
    
    Match style.text_color:
        When Optional.Some with value as color:
            Call Dict.set with dict as style_dict and key as "text_color" and value as color_to_string with color as color
        When Optional.None:
            Pass
    
    Match style.font_size:
        When Optional.Some with value as size:
            Call Dict.set with dict as style_dict and key as "font_size" and value as size
        When Optional.None:
            Pass
    
    Match style.font_family:
        When Optional.Some with value as family:
            Call Dict.set with dict as style_dict and key as "font_family" and value as family
        When Optional.None:
            Pass
    
    Return style_dict

Process called "color_to_string" that takes color as UIColor returns String:
    Match color:
        When RGB with red as r and green as g and blue as b:
            Return "rgb(" Joined with r as String Joined with "," Joined with g as String Joined with "," Joined with b as String Joined with ")"
        When RGBA with red as r and green as g and blue as b and alpha as a:
            Return "rgba(" Joined with r as String Joined with "," Joined with g as String Joined with "," Joined with b as String Joined with "," Joined with a as String Joined with ")"
        When Named with color as name:
            Return name
        Otherwise:
            Return "black"  Note: Default fallback color